  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "スーパーファミコン用のオンラインサービスソフトです。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "XBAND (stylized as XBⱯND) was one of the first competitive online console gaming networks and was available for the Genesis and Super NES. It was produced by Catapult Entertainment in Cupertino, California. It is the only modem released in America to have been officially licensed by Nintendo. It debuted in various areas of the United States between November 1994 and June 1995 and was later released nationwide between October 2 and 8, 1995.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
